<H3> <TI>   UNITA Claims Plane Shot Down </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNITA Claims Plane Shot Down </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2806073794 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 0600 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2806073794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Military sources say National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola [UNITA] antiaircraft forces shot down a 
Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola-Labor Party 
[MPLA-PT] airplane in Huila Province on 26 June 1994. The 
sources say a Russian-made MiG-23 was hit while attacking 
civilian targets in Ngola region, north of Lubango. It all 
happened at about 1240. After being hit the aircraft tried to 
return to the Lubango Air Force Base, but exploded near the 
runway, killing all its crew. The sources added that UNITA 
armed forces are able to thwart the MPLA-PT's air force 
arrogance. 
  Meanwhile, it has been reported that fierce clashes took 
place in Huila Province where the MPLA-PT is involved in 
military offensives against UNITA. In defensive operations 
carried out by UNITA's Armed Forces for the Liberation of 
Angola, an MPLA motorized convoy was attacked on the road 
between Cacula and [name indistinct]. 
  Our forces killed 14 MPLA-PT soldiers and wounded 32 others. 
UNITA also captured MPLA Major Manuel Bravante Ngongo, born in 
Pambangala, Cuanza Sul Province's Cassongue District. Maj. 
Ngongo was the commander of the 4th Motorized Infantry Battalion 
stationed in Cacula and the leading officer behind the offensive 
in the northern region of Huila Province. 

</TEXT>

