BFN 

  [Excerpts] On the occasion of the celebration of the 19th 
aniversary of national independence, President of the Republic 
Joaquim Chissano said that the issue of an eventual government 
of national unity has not been definitely put aside. [passage 
omitted] 
  The president of the Republic also said he was not worried 
about his fate or that of his party in the forthcoming 
elections. Chissano said: I would only be very worried if there 
was another war in Mozambique. I am not worried about whether I 
will continue as the country's president. The president added 
that he would be worried if we failed to create a better future, 
which is our challenge for the future. He said the forthcoming 
elections should bring the results wished for by the Mozambican 
people. 

