<H3> <TI>   Government Needs $950 Million To Repair Roads </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Needs $950 Million To Repair Roads </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB2406185194 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
1030 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2406185194 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mozambique needs $950 million to repair roads over a 
five-year period. Construction and Water Minister Joao Salomao 
said the money will be used to rehabilitate about 29,000 km of 
the national road network. The minister also said that about 80 
percent of the budget will be used for repair work, opening of 
