  [Text] Cape Town June 27 SAPA -- Minister of Sport Mr Steve 
Tshwete has been appointed acting minister of education while 
the minister, Professor Sibusiso Bhengu, recovers from a mild 
stroke he suffered last Thursday [23 June], President Nelson 
Mandela announced Monday. Mr Mandela said after visiting Prof 
Bhengu in a Cape Town clinic that he was making an "excellent 
recovery". "Professor Bhengu is able to walk around and 
communicate. His physicians have, however, advised that he 
should rest for a few weeks. The government of national unity 
and I wish Professor Bhengu a speedy recovery." Mr Tshwete 
would act until he recovered sufficiently to resume his duties, 
the president said. 

