BFN 

  [Excerpt] The French soldiers yesterday pushed their 
patrols forward as far as 20 km from battlefields in Gikongoro 
Prefecture. According to Captain Emmanuel Ndahiro of the Rwandan 
Patriotic Army [RPA], French soldiers found to be standing in 
RPA's way will be asked to account for it. 
  Although Paris describes the present mission as a 
humanitarian one, nobody is fooled by the real intentions of its 
intervention which is to protect criminals. Moreover, these 
criminals have started (?rejoicing). Prime Minister Kambanda, 
the so-called prime minister, for example, announced clearly the 
day before the French troops landed in Goma and Bukavu in 
eastern Zaire, that his men had received new consignments of 
arms which would enable them to celebrate the 32nd independence 
anniversary in Kigali on 1 July. [passage omitted]. 

