<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Somalia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Says People Tired of Civil War </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Says People Tired of Civil War </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2906130094 (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the 
Great Somali People in Somali 1700 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2906130094 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the 
Great Somali People </F>

<F P=105>  Somali </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ongoing talks among intellectuals and elders of 
Mogadishu indicate that they do not wish to see a resumption of 
fighting among the brotherly Somali people. This was stated by 
Ali Mohamed Ugas Ali, member of the United Somali Congress [USC] 
Central Committee. 
  Ugas Ali, who was speaking to reporters from Radio 
Mogadishu, 
the voice of the Somali people, said there are a few 
self-seekers who are bent on creating trouble among the Somali 
people but that they now understand the value of peace and are 
tired of the agony of civil war. Ugas Ali added that the 
intellectuals and elders are working to unite against all the 
causes of insecurity. 
  Concluding, Ali Mohamed Ugas Ali stressed that Somalis in 
general, and those in Mogadishu in particular, should be extra 
alert to the traps being laid by those wishing to start 
senseless fighting. He added that efforts should be made 
towards healing the wounds of the past. 

</TEXT>

