<H3> <TI>   Ghanaian ECOMOG Reportedly Impounds LPC Arms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ghanaian ECOMOG Reportedly Impounds LPC Arms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2906190094 Gbarnga Radio ELRL in English 1400 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2906190094 </F>
<F P=104>  Gbarnga Radio ELRL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ghanaian contingent of ECOMOG [Economic 
Community of West African States Cease-Fire Monitoring Group] 
has reportedly arrested several truckloads of arms and 
ammunition on the Monrovia- Buchanan Highway. According to the 
reports, the consignment of arms and ammunition was intended for 
the Liberian Peace Council [LPC], and was being escorted to 
Buchanan by the Nigerian contingent of ECOMOG. This exposure by 
the Ghanaian contingent proves what the NPFL [National Patriotic 
Front of Liberia] and Africa Watch have revealed that the 
Nigerian contingent of ECOMOG is the sole supplier of arms and 
ammunition to the LPC in its onslaught against the Liberian 
people in southeast Liberia. 
  In a related development, military personnel of the NPFL 
recently intercepted large quantities of arms and ammunition 
from members of the LPC, which had been delivered by the 
Nigerian ECOMOG soldiers during late hours of the night. 

</TEXT>

