<F P=104>  Gbarnga Radio ELRL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Internal Affairs Minister Samuel Dhokie, as part of 
his clandestine operation to launch an attack on positions of 
the NPFL [National Patriotic Front of Liberia], is reported to 
have visited Guinea. Mr. Samuel Dhokie, according to reports, 
visited Guinea to seek cooperation from local Guinean 
authorities for the use of Guinean soil for his planned attack, 
under the guise of arranging the repatriation of Liberian 
refugees there. But he is reported to have been refused any 
cooperation from the Guinean Government. 
  The NPFL controversial nominee to the Liberian National 
Transitional Government, who cut short his trip to Guinea as a 
result of the refusal of authorities there to cooperate with 
him, visited many refugee camps seeking support for his 
so-called Nimba Defense Force. Observers are questioning the 
credibility of Minister Dhokie and his cohorts, accusing them of 
working contrary to the social peace of Liberia and their 
original organizations that nominated them. There are even 
calls for their replacement. 

</TEXT>

