<H3> <TI>   NPFL Demands Investigation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NPFL Demands Investigation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2906170294 Gbarnga Radio ELRL in English 1400 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2906170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Gbarnga Radio ELRL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The NPFL [National Patriotic Front of Liberia] is 
calling for an immediate investigation within the State Council 
that some transitional ministers are planning an attack on NPFL 
positions. Recently, intelligence reports revealed that some 
LNTG [Liberia National Transition Government] ministers had a 
meeting in Guinea, in an attempt to destabilize the ongoing 
peace process. The report said these ministers are financing 
armed groups to attack Nimba and Bong counties from Guinea. The 
NPFL said any attack out of Guinea will meet with reciprocal 
action. 
  In a letter to Guinean President Lansana Conte, NPFL leader 
Charles Gankay Taylor urged him not to allow his territory to be 
used as a springboard for launching attacks on Liberia. He said 
any covert assistance by Guinea to armed groups attempting to 
derail the peace process in Liberia, will amount to a violation 
of international law and an encroachment on the territorial 
integrity of Liberia. President Taylor said the brotherly 
relations between Guinea and Liberia will continue, and a few 
power-seekers and unpatriotic citizens of Liberia should not be 
allowed to destroy the lives of peoples of the two countries. 

</TEXT>

