<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Togo </F>
<H3> <TI>   France Resumes Economic, Military Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    France Resumes Economic, Military Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2906223394 Lome Radio Lome in French 1900 GMT 29 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2906223394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lome Radio Lome </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] France is resuming cooperation with Togo. This 
was announced in Paris this morning by Richard Dequesne, a 
spokesman for the French Foreign Affairs Ministry. The French 
Government believes that the crisis has ended in Togo, and has 
decided to resume civil and military cooperation with our 
country. This cooperation had been suspended at the end of 
1992. The French Government noted that, up to now, the long 
political crisis experienced in Togo did not permit them to 
engage in palliative measures to cushion the impact of the 
devaluation of the CFA franc, as was done for all other franc 
zone countries. These measures were essential to the country's 
economic and financial balance. 
  The French Government also announced that, to show its 
solidarity with the Togolese people, it has decided to resume 
its cooperation, and called on its European Union partners to 
follow suit. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

