<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Mozambique </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Denies Land Allocated to Maharishi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Denies Land Allocated to Maharishi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MB3006092394 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
0500 GMT 30 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB3006092394 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Finance Minister Eneias Comiche has told the 
MOZAMBIQUE INFORMATION AGENCY, AIM, that the Mozambican 
Government has not allocated 20 million hectares of land to the 
Maharishi Heaven on Earth Development Corporation based in the 
Netherlands. However, Comiche confirmed that last year the 
Mozambican Government and that organization signed an agreement. 
The finance minister said that contrary to reports made by a 
number of Mozambican and foreign journalists over the past few 
days that 20 million hectares of land were allocated to the 
organization, this agreement does not allocate or grant to the 
organization a specific portion of land in Mozambique. Eneias 
Comiche added that if the corporation chooses to carry out 
ventures in Mozambique, it will have to follow all the 
procedures stipulated by the current laws in the country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

