<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Congo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Forces, Opposition Clash in Pila </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Forces, Opposition Clash in Pila </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2806185094 Libreville Africa No. 1 in French 1215 GMT 28 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2806185094 </F>
<F P=104>  Libreville Africa No. 1 </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Fresh clashes occurred between opposition supporters 
and security forces in the Congolese capital Brazzaville. At 
least two people were killed in Pila in the eastern part of 
Brazzaville. Tension seems to have ebbed but sporadic shots from 
automatic weapons were still heard last night at Pila considered 
as the stronghold of the supporters of former President Sassou 
Nguesso. This new tension followed the kidnapping last Saturday 
of two sympathizers of the Presidential Group in Bacongo in the 
sourthen part of Brazzaville and stronghold of the members of 
the Congolese Movement for Democracy and Integral Development 
led by Bernard Kolelas. 

</TEXT>

