<H3> <TI>   UDI Federal Headquarters Attacked; Leader Comments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UDI Federal Headquarters Attacked; Leader Comments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AB2906114094 Kinshasa Voix du Zaire in French 1800 GMT 28 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2906114094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kinshasa Voix du Zaire </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The federal office of the Union of Independent 
Democrats [UDI] at Matonge in the Kalamu Area was the target of 
a terrorist attack in the night of 24 June. A locally made bomb 
set in the building exploded. There was no loss of human lives 
but property damage has been reported. This was disclosed by 
Mr. (Tambo Mwamba), UDI national chairman. He was speaking this 
morning at a news briefing he held before reporters of 
state-owned and private media organs. The speaker said this is 
the fourth time his party has been the victim of acts of 
violence. He observed that his party has sufficient material 
means to react, but in a democracy people must express views and 
discuss or advance convincing arguments. It is not advisable to 
resort to violence in the event of disagreement on a viewpoint, 
UDI Chairman (Tambo Mwamba) concluded, adding that he is looking 
forward to the findings of the inquiry on the bomb attack [words 
indistinct]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

