<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conference on Economic Reforms Opens in Beijing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conference on Economic Reforms Opens in Beijing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2705133194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1242 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2705133194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 27 (XINHUA) -- An International Academy 
of Management conference was held here this morning, focusing on 
economic reforms in China. 
  Pedro Nueno, chancellor of the International Academy of 
Management, and Jing Shuping, managing director of the China 
International Trust and Investment Corporation and president of 
the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce, made opening 
speeches. 
  This is the academy's first conference in China. It has been 
sponsored by the International Academy of Management, China 
International Economic Consultants Ltd., and the China-Europe 
Management Institute. 
  Representatives from 11 countries at the gathering are 
discussing such issues as China's current economic reform 
policy, securities, using overseas investments, and financial, 
taxation and state-owned enterprises reforms. 
  The International Academy of Management, set up in 1958, has 
232 members from 34 countries. The current conference is aimed 
to promote the academy's study of China's economic reforms and 
development. 

</TEXT>

