<H3> <TI>   Rong Yiren Meets Economic Reform Conference Participants </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rong Yiren Meets Economic Reform Conference Participants </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2805042794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0400 GMT 28 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2805042794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 28 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-President 
Rong Yiren met with foreign participants of the symposium on 
China's economic reforms at the Great Hall of the People here 
this morning. 
  The symposium opened here yesterday. Its sponsors included 
the International Academy of Management (IAM), China 
International Economic Consultants, Inc. (CIEC), and the China 
Europe Management Institute. 
  Rong said that he was pleased with the symposium and 
expressed congratulations to its success. 
  Briefing guests on China's economic growth, Rong said that 
in 
building a socialist market economy, China attaches much 
importance to the absorbing of foreign management expertise. 
  He asked foreign management experts to give their valuable 
advice as often as possible. 
  IAM President Pedro Nueno said that the symposium helped him 
and his colleagues acquire more knowledge about China's economic 
growth. China promises a very bright future, he said. 
  Founded in 1985, IAM boasts of over 200 members from 34 
countries. 
  CIEC President Jing Shuping took part in the meeting. 

</TEXT>

