<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zou Jiahua Says Sino-Foreign Cooperation Mutually Beneficial </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zou Jiahua Says Sino-Foreign Cooperation Mutually Beneficial </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2805155794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1519 GMT 28 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2805155794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 28 (XINHUA) -- Sino-foreign 
cooperation should uphold the principle of being mutually 
beneficial and Marching toward long-term stable relations, 
Chinese Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua said here today. 
  He made these remarks while meeting with foreign delegates 
attending an international seminar on China's new investment 
style of "B.O.T. (build, operate and transfer)". 
  China's reform and opening to the outside world demand a 
peaceful international environment and China is willing to 
cultivate economic cooperation with foreign nations and 
international organizations, the vice-premier said. 
  Each party should make use of its own strengths in the 
cooperation, he said, adding that many Western countries have 
advanced technology, management systems and abundant capital, 
which could be combined with China's rich natural resources. 
  In addition, he said, China has established a certain 
economic basis. The country also has a huge market potential 
and its labor costs are lower. 
  The combination of both parties will be mutually beneficial, 
he said. 
  The vice-premier told the delegates that China is willing to 
cooperate with foreign partners in various forms, including the 
"B.O.T.", which is quite "acceptable". 
  Senior executives from the World Bank, the Asian Development 
Bank and other international organizations as well as 
internationally prominent companies participated in the seminar, 
which was sponsored by the State Planning Commission. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

