<H3> <TI>   Romanian Parliament Leaders Receive Chinese Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Romanian Parliament Leaders Receive Chinese Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2405035494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0157 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2405035494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, May 23 (XINHUA) -- Leaders of the 
Romanian Parliament stressed here today that the further growth 
of friendly relations between Romania and China will contribute 
to the interests of both nations and to world stability. 
  At a meeting with visiting members of the Chinese parliament 
led by Zhou Jue, member of the Chinese National People's 
Congress, Romanian Senate President Liviu Gherman said that the 
two nations have a long history of friendly ties and these 
relations should be further developed. 
  He said that increased contact between the two parliaments 
will promote economic reforms in both countries. 
  At a separate meeting with the Chinese delegation the same 
day, Adrian Nastase, president of the Romanian Chamber of 
Deputies, said that strengthened relations between the two 
parliaments is in accord with the political and economic 
interests of the two nations and the demands of the current 
international situation. 
  The Chinese delegation arrived here on Sunday [22 May] for a 
four-day goodwill visit to the East European nation. During 
their stay here they will also hold talks with officials from 
the Ministries of Foreign Affairs, Trade and Tourism. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

