<H3> <TI>   Guangzhou Holds Photo Exhibit on Deng Xiaoping </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guangzhou Holds Photo Exhibit on Deng Xiaoping </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2805141394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1336 GMT 28 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2805141394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, May 28 (XINHUA) -- An exhibition of 
photographs depicting the historic activities and daily life of 
Deng Xiaoping opened in Guangzhou on Saturday [28 May]. 
  Xie Fei, member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central 
Committee and secretary of Guangdong Provincial Committee of the 
CPC, took part in the opening ceremony. 
  The exhibition of more than 520 photos record Deng's 
activities in the period of the new democratic revolution and in 
the construction of socialist China. 
  Pictures depicting Deng's political activities and daily 
life 
since China began to carry out the policy of reform and opening 
are especially displayed, including his successive inspection 
tours of Guangdong and his inspection of south China in 1992. 

</TEXT>

