<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shenzhen Foreign Exchange Trading Center Starts Business </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shenzhen Foreign Exchange Trading Center Starts Business </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2805150594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1444 GMT 28 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2805150594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shenzhen, May 28 (XINHUA) -- Shenzhen Foreign 
Exchange Trading Center started business today. 
  The center, in south China's Guangdong Province, is the 
first 
of its kind. It is authorized to buy and sell foreign exchange, 
to conduct transactions in bills of exchange, borrowing and 
lending of foreign currencies, services connected with 
investment in foreign exchange and consultancy on development 
trends of foreign exchange. 
  Enterprises and individuals on the Chinese mainland will be 
able to maintain the value of their foreign exchange and prevent 
any risks in foreign exchange through operations at the center, 
XINHUA was told by officials of the center. 
  The officials said the center has got financial legal status 
with a membership system, and it has a registered capital of 100 
million yuan. At present, it has 14 banks and financial 
organizations as its member share-holders. 

</TEXT>

