<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hainan Secretary Meets Hong Kong Trade Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hainan Secretary Meets Hong Kong Trade Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2605120294 Haikou Hainan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2605120294 </F>
<F P=104>  Haikou Hainan People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday afternoon, Ruan Chongwu, provincial party 
committee secretary and governor, met in China Hainan Reform and 
Development Research Institute with a 12-member Hong Kong Trade 
Development Council [TDC] delegation headed by Francis Lo, Hong 
Kong TDC executive director, and Mary Wong, Hong Kong TDC 
assistant executive director. 
  During the meeting, Ruan Chongwu briefed the Hong Kong 
guests 
on Hainan's investment environment, preferential taxation 
policies, and convenient and efficient enterprise registration 
process. 
  The Hong Kong TDC delegation expressed profound interest in 
Hainan's development prospects. 
  Over the next few days, the Hong Kong TDC delegation will 
hold separate talks with Hainan's economic cooperation, 
commercial and trade, and financial and banking departments on a 
number of cooperation projects. 
  Persons in charge of the provincial economic cooperation 
department, commercial and trade department, foreign affairs 
office, and other departments concerned were also present during 
the meeting. 

