<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Treasury Bonds Reportedly Sold Out at End of May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Treasury Bonds Reportedly Sold Out at End of May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2705162394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1428 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2705162394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 27 (XINHUA) -- The planned amount of 
27 billion yuan worth of two-year state treasury bonds for this 
year was sold out by the end of May 25, five days earlier than 
the target date, according to sources from the Ministry of 
Finance here today. 
  In addition, the public have purchased about 40.25 billion 
yuan three-year bonds so far, accounting for 67 percent of the 
total issue of 60 billion yuan. 
  Treasury bond sales has been rather smooth this year, thanks 
to the sound economic environment and swelling personal purses, 
said a finance official in charge of the issue. 
  He was confident that the remaining 20 billion three-year 
bonds would be sold out by the end of June as planned. 
  The interest rate for 1994 two-year treasury bonds is 13 
percent, and 13.96 percent for three-year ones. Both are higher 
than the interest rates for bank deposits of the same term. 

</TEXT>

