<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister of Railways Says Firms Diversifying </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister of Railways Says Firms Diversifying </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2805073994 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in English 0334 
GMT 28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2805073994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 28 (CNS) -- Minister of Railways, Mr 
Han Zhubin, recently revealed that diversified business had 
become an important economic pillar of railway enterprises in 
China. 
  After more than ten years' development, railway enterprises 
in the country have developed their business from the mere 
railway industry to a dozen of industries including commerce, 
trade, tourism, food and catering, storage and construction. 
The diversified business has not only offered an economic 
backing to the construction and development of railways in the 
country, but also streamlined staff and workers in the railway 
sector, creating relaxed conditions for the reform of railway 
enterprises. 
  The diversified business of railway enterprises started in 
1984 and by the end of last year, there were over 7,000 
enterprises engaging in diversified business with employment of 
more than 380,000. Business income earned by them in 1993 made 
up nearly half of the total earned from railway shipment while 
their profits surpassed that from railway shipment. According 
to statistics, the diversified business income between 1986 and 
1993 was RMB [renminbi] 75.7 billion and some 218,000 staff and 
workers originally engaging in railway shipment had been 
transferred to enterprises specializing in other businesses. 
  The minister said that the goal set for the railway sector's 
diversified business in the next 6 years was to increase its 
business income and sales value as well as profits all by four 
times and streamline another hundreds of thousands of staff and 
workers from shipment enterprises to diversified business ones. 
[sentence as published] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

