<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cities Take Lead in Electrical Appliance Ownership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cities Take Lead in Electrical Appliance Ownership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK3005131094 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0818 GMT 
30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK3005131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 30 (CNS) -- According to a survey 
conducted by the Consumers Committee of the China Quality 
Management Association and the Beijing Shiqing Market 
Consultancy to 5,120 households in Beijing, Shanghai and 
Guangzhou, the three municipalities are now taking a lead in the 
country in terms of households' possession rate of colour TV 
sets, hi-fi sets, refrigerators, air conditioners, automatic 
washing machines, electric fans and water heaters. 
  The possession rate of colour TV sets by households in these 
cities has reached 97.4 percent, that of refrigerators 95.7 
percent, that of electric fans 90.7 percent and that of water 
heaters 58.7 percent. Such a possession rate of hi-fi sets is 
25.3 percent in Beijing, 23.8 percent in Shanghai and 45 percent 
in Guangzhou. Owing to the regional weather differences, the 
possession rate of air conditioners is 4.6 percent in Beijing, 
14.5 percent in Shanghai and 34.9 percent in Guangzhou, while 
the average rate of this machine in these three cities is 16.3 
percent. 

</TEXT>

