<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sichuan Popularizes Agricultural Technology </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sichuan Popularizes Agricultural Technology </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3005015994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0141 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3005015994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chengdu, May 30 (XINHUA) -- Southwest China's 
Sichuan Province has been engaged in popularizing agricultural 
science and technology and has consequently reaped bumper 
harvests over the past few years. 
  According to statistics from the agricultural department of 
the province, grain output increased by 1.3 billion kg and the 
farmers obtained a total extra income of 588 million yuan last 
year by utilizing the new technologies and techniques. 
  As the major pork production base of the country, the 
province has spread scientific pig-raising techniques. Animal 
husbandry in the province has been developing for 17 years 
running. 
  The province produced 4.l49 million tons of pork last year, 
3.33 percent more than in 1992. 
  From the beginning of this year, the provincial committee of 
science and technology, the provincial agricultural academy, 
Southwest China Agriculture University in the province and 
Sichuan Agriculture University have sent 100 scientists and 
technicians to grassroots units to contract a total area of 
10,000 mu (about 666 hectares) to set examples of high-yield 
farmlands for the local peasants. 
  Since 1990, governmental organs also sent more than 2,200 
officials to comparatively backward counties to help residents 
to shake off poverty. 
  Thousands of technicians from large enterprises work in 
township enterprises to help them develop products and seek 
markets. 

</TEXT>

