<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tibet Officials Attend Military Service Law Forum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tibet Officials Attend Military Service Law Forum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2905034194 Lhasa Tibet Television Network in Mandarin 1200 
GMT 28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2905034194 </F>
<F P=104>  Lhasa Tibet Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Station report by Renqing (0088 7230), Qimei (0366 5019), </F>
and Dawa (6671 1216) from the "Regional News Hookup" program; 
reporters' names shown in caption] 
  [Text] On the afternoon of 27 May, the Tibetan People's 
Armed Forces Committee, the Tibetan Military District [TMD], and 
the regional party committee's Propaganda Department jointly 
held a forum in Lhasa to mark the 10th anniversary of the 
promulgation of the present Military Service Law. Regional 
party, government, and military leaders Raidi, Puqung, (Cui 
Jiguo), Laba Pingcuo, Luosang Toinzhub, Zhou Wenbi, Hu Yongzhu, 
Gama Cedain, Jiang Chengguang, and concerned leaders from 
various regional departments and bureaus attended the forum. 
  Regional Vice Chairman Laba Pingcuo addressed the forum. He 
said: Since the present Military Service Law was promulgated 10 
years ago, party and government organizations at all levels 
across the region have been carrying out the propaganda and 
implementation of the law as a strategic task for improving the 
understanding of national defense among the masses of all 
nationalities in the region and enhancing their awareness of the 
need for national defense, and have been taking the support for 
national defense and army building as an important element in 
stabilizing the situation and developing the economy. They gave 
full support to military families accompanying the troops, 
helping them to get jobs and education for their children. Over 
the past decade, the vast number of cadres and the masses -- 
after acquainting themselves with the basic guidelines of the 
Military Service Law -- enhanced their understanding of national 
defense and of the great significance of strengthening army 
building and national defense and inspired youngsters' patriotic 
zeal and enthusiasm in supporting and joining the Army, bringing 
about a favorable general mood in society to support and show 
concern for national defense building and to support, cherish, 
and honor the people's own Army. 
  TMD Commander Zhou Wenbi and leaders from the regional party 
committee Propaganda Department, the regional justice 
department, and other relevant units also spoke at the forum. 

</TEXT>

