<H3> <TI>   Malaysia's Mohamed Confident of Increase of Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Malaysia's Mohamed Confident of Increase of Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3005172694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1708 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3005172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, May 30 (XINHUA) -- Malaysian Prime 
Minister Mahathir Mohamed is confident that the uptrend of 
Malaysian-Chinese relations will be further reinforced in the 
future. 
  He said this in his message to his Chinese counterpart Li 
Peng today on the occasion of the 20th anniversary (May 31) of 
the founding of the diplomatic relations between the two 
countries. 
  "Links between Malaysia and China actually stretched a long 
way back into history, but it is only over the last two decades 
that our bilateral relationship has reached a new level of 
understanding and cooperation," Mahathir said. 
  "The policy of friendly relations with neighboring countries 
has encouraged positive developments in our bilateral relations, 
particularly in recent years," he said. 
  He added: "In the past five years or so, bilateral relations 
have increased by leaps and bounds in many fields of cooperation. 
  "I am confident that this trend will be further reinforced 
in 
the years to come. Aside from the rapid increase in economic 
cooperation, trade and investment, cooperation in other fields 
such as tourism, cultural exchanges and people-to-people 
contacts will further encourage better understanding and 
friendship between Malaysia and China." 

</TEXT>

