  [Text] Taipei, May 27 (CNA) -- Premier Lien Chan has 
decided to leave for Central America on Sunday [29 May], one day 
earlier than originally scheduled, the Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs announced Friday. 
  Lien will make a stopover in Los Angeles on Monday, and in 
Miami on Tuesday on his way to El Salvador, where he is 
scheduled to attend the inauguration ceremony of newly elected 
President Armando Calderon Sol on Wednesday. He will proceed to 
Guatemala on Thursday. 
  During his visit in Guatemala, Lien will discuss issues of 
mutual concern with Guatemalan President Ramiro de Leon Carpio, 
who will confer a medal of special order on Lien. 
