<H3> <TI>   President Asks Industrialists To Help Development </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Asks Industrialists To Help Development </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3105072194 Taipei CNA in English 0640 GMT 31 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3105072194 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Y. C. Tsai] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, May 31 (CNA) -- President Li Teng-hui 
Monday [30 May] called on leading industrialists to help develop 
Taiwan's industrial base in order to ensure continued economic 
growth and boost domestic competitiveness in international 
markets. 
  Li made the statement while meeting with a group of 20 
industrialists, headed by Chairman Kao Ching-yuan of the Chinese 
National Federation of Industries. 
  To seek further progress, Li said, the industrial sector 
should learn how to make the best use of its resources and 
stress personnel training as well as research and development. 
  The government will cooperate with the industrial sector in 
mapping out appropriate policies and laws to help domestic 
industries cope with challenges and competition from abroad, Li 
pledged. 
  Various phases of economic development call for different 
strategies, he added. 
  Li talked with the industrialists on a variety of economic 
and noneconomic issues, including financing, investment, the 
national health insurance program, the introduction of foreign 
laborers to Taiwan, environmental protection, and Taiwan's entry 
into GATT. 
  Among the industrial representatives were President Liu 
Kuo-chao of the Taiwan Electric Appliance Manufacturers 
Association, President Lu Chi-sheng of the Taiwan Association of 
Machinery Industry, and Chairman Wang Yiu-tzeng of the China 
Rebar Group. 
  The president said that he was happy to exchange views with 
the industrialists. Noting he has already met with delegates 
from the agricultural and fishery sectors, he said he will also 
meet with business and labor [passage indistinct] the Chinese 
Federation of Labor on June 10. 

</TEXT>

