<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Views Hungarian Election, Cambodia Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Views Hungarian Election, Cambodia Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW3005122094 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1146 
GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW3005122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 30 May (XINHUA) -- A Foreign Ministry 
spokesman answered reporters' questions here today. 
  Question [Q]: What are your comments on the victory of the 
Hungarian Socialist Party in the national parliamentary election? 
  Answer [A]: The Hungarian election is an internal affair of 
Hungary. We respect the choice made by the Hungarian people. We 
hope and believe that relations between China and Hungary in the 
political, economic, and cultural fields will develop in a 
sustained, steady, and all-around manner on the basis of the 
five principles of peaceful co-existence. 
  Q: What are your comments on the round-table talks on peace 
and national reconciliation in Cambodia held in Pyonyang? 
  A: The holding of the Cambodia round-table talks is 
conducive to peace and national reconciliation in Cambodia. We 
appreciate and support the efforts made by King Sihanouk to this 
end and sincerely hope that the Government of the Kingdom of 
Cambodia and the Democratic Kampuchea side will set store by the 
overall national interests and continue to seek a proper 
settlement of their internal dispute through consultations. 

</TEXT>

