<H3> <TI>   Hong Kong, Sweden Sign Investment Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hong Kong, Sweden Sign Investment Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2705161794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1520 GMT 27 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2705161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, May 27 (XINHUA) -- An agreement aimed at 
promoting and protecting mutual investment between Hong Kong and 
Sweden was signed here today. 
  Speaking at the signing ceremony, T.H. Chau, secretary for 
trade and industry, said that the agreement would further 
strengthen the excellent economic ties between the two areas. 
  According to Chau, the agreement provides investors from 
both 
sides with guarantees of fair treatment, the unrestricted right 
to transfer investments and returns, and proper compensation in 
the event of losses owing to expropriation. 
  The agreement, the fourth of its kind Hong Kong has signed, 
will enter into force 30 days after signature and remain 
effective for an initial period of 15 years. 

</TEXT>

